2. Data Preprocessing

Import data into a dataframe

In[3]:
df = pd.read_csv("resources/creditcard.csv")

This is an extract from the Kaggle source explaining the dataset values.

"Features V1 to V28 are the principal components obtained with PCA, the only features which have not been transformed with PCA are 'Time' and 'Amount'. Feature 'Time' contains the seconds elapsed between each transaction and the first transaction in the dataset. The feature 'Amount' is the transaction Amount, this feature can be used for example-dependant cost-sensitive learning. Feature 'Class' is the response variable and it takes value 1 in case of fraud and 0 otherwise."

from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

# Function to extract x and y
def get_x_y(dataframe):
    x = dataframe.drop('Class', axis=1)
    y = dataframe['Class']
    return x, y

# Function to split data into train, test, and validation sets
def split_data(x, y, rs):

    # Test data size = 20%
    test_size = 0.2

    # Validation data size = 20% (will be 25% of training data)
    val_size = 0.25
    
    # First split: train and test
    x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
        x, y, test_size=test_size, random_state=rs, stratify=y
    )
    # Second split: train and validation from the train set
    x_train, x_val, y_train, y_val = train_test_split(
        x_train, y_train, test_size=val_size, random_state=rs, stratify=y_train
    )
    return x_train, x_val, x_test, y_train, y_val, y_test

# Master function to process a dataset
def process_dataset(dataframe, rs):
    x, y = get_x_y(dataframe)  # Extract features and target
    return split_data(x, y, rs)

# Example usage for the original and log-transformed datasets
df_splits = process_dataset(df, 42)        # For the non-log dataset

# Unpacking the splits for clarity
df_x_train, df_x_val, df_x_test, df_y_train, df_y_val, df_y_test = df_splits

In[17]:
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, roc_auc_score, confusion_matrix


# Function to initialize the Logistic Regression model
def init_lr_model(x, y, class_weight, random_state):
    model = LogisticRegression(
        class_weight=class_weight, 
        random_state=random_state
    )
    model.fit(x, y)
    return model

# Function to evaluate the model
def eval_lr_model(title, pred, prob, y_val):
    auroc = roc_auc_score(y_val, prob)
    cr = classification_report(y_val, pred, target_names=['Not Fraud', 'Fraud'])
    cm = confusion_matrix(y_val, pred)
    print(title)
    print("AUC-ROC:", auroc)
    print("Classification Report:\n", cr)
    print("Confusion Matrix:\n", cm)
    return auroc, cr, cm

# Function to predict and create results
def create_lr_results(model, x_val, y_val, output_title):
    pred = model.predict(x_val)
    prob = model.predict_proba(x_val)[:, 1]
    model_auroc, model_cr, model_cm = eval_lr_model(output_title, pred, prob, y_val)
    return model_auroc, model_cr, model_cm

from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, roc_auc_score, confusion_matrix

# Function to initialize the Random Forest model
def init_rf_model(x, y, class_weight, random_state=42, n_estimators=100):
    model = RandomForestClassifier(
        class_weight=class_weight, 
        random_state=random_state, 
        n_estimators=n_estimators
    )
    model.fit(x, y)
    return model

# Function to evaluate the model
def eval_rf_model(title, pred, prob, y_val):
    auroc = roc_auc_score(y_val, prob)
    cr = classification_report(y_val, pred, target_names=['Not Fraud', 'Fraud'])
    cm = confusion_matrix(y_val, pred)
    print(title)
    print("AUC-ROC:", auroc)
    print("Classification Report:\n", cr)
    print("Confusion Matrix:\n", cm)
    return auroc, cr, cm

# Function to predict and create results
def create_rf_results(model, x_val, y_val, output_title):
    pred = model.predict(x_val)
    prob = model.predict_proba(x_val)[:, 1]  # Probability for Fraud (class 1)
    model_auroc, model_cr, model_cm = eval_rf_model(output_title, pred, prob, y_val)
    return model_auroc, model_cr, model_cm

from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve, auc
from sklearn.metrics import precision_recall_curve, average_precision_score
from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix

def plot_roc_curve(y_true, y_prob, title):
    fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_true, y_prob)
    roc_auc = auc(fpr, tpr)
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label=f'AUC = {roc_auc:.2f}', linewidth=2)
    plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--', linewidth=1, label='Random Guess')
    plt.title(f'ROC Curve - {title}')
    plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
    plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
    plt.legend(loc='lower right')
    plt.grid()
    plt.show()

def plot_precision_recall_curve(y_true, y_prob, title):
    precision, recall, _ = precision_recall_curve(y_true, y_prob)
    avg_precision = average_precision_score(y_true, y_prob)
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    plt.plot(recall, precision, label=f'Avg Precision = {avg_precision:.2f}', linewidth=2)
    plt.title(f'Precision-Recall Curve - {title}')
    plt.xlabel('Recall')
    plt.ylabel('Precision')
    plt.legend(loc='lower left')
    plt.grid()
    plt.show()

def plot_confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred, title):
    cm = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred)
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 5))
    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues', xticklabels=['Not Fraud', 'Fraud'], yticklabels=['Not Fraud', 'Fraud'])
    plt.title(f'Confusion Matrix - {title}')
    plt.xlabel('Predicted')
    plt.ylabel('Actual')
    plt.show()

from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense, Dropout, Input
from tensorflow.keras.callbacks import EarlyStopping
from sklearn.metrics import roc_auc_score, classification_report, confusion_matrix

# Define DNN model with an explicit Input layer
def build_dnn_model(input_dim):
    model = Sequential([
        Input(shape=(input_dim,)),  # Explicit input layer
        Dense(128, activation='relu'),
        Dropout(0.3),
        Dense(64, activation='relu'),
        Dropout(0.3),
        Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')  # Output layer for binary classification
    ])
    return model

# Compile the model
def compile_dnn_model(model):
    model.compile(
        optimizer='adam',
        loss='binary_crossentropy',
        metrics=['accuracy']
    )
    return model

# Train the model
def train_dnn_model(model, x_train, y_train, x_val, y_val, epochs=30, batch_size=64):
    early_stopping = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=5, restore_best_weights=True)
    history = model.fit(
        x_train, y_train,
        validation_data=(x_val, y_val),
        epochs=epochs,
        batch_size=batch_size,
        callbacks=[early_stopping],
        verbose=1
    )
    return history

# Evaluate the model
def evaluate_dnn_model(title, model, x_val, y_val):
    y_val_pred = (model.predict(x_val) > 0.5).astype(int)
    y_val_prob = model.predict(x_val)
    print(title)
    print("AUC-ROC:", roc_auc_score(y_val, y_val_prob))
    print("Classification Report:\n", classification_report(y_val, y_val_pred, target_names=['Not Fraud', 'Fraud']))
    print("Confusion Matrix:\n", confusion_matrix(y_val, y_val_pred))

def build_generator(noise_dim, feature_dim):
    # Noise input
    input_noise = layers.Input(shape=(noise_dim,))
    # Class label input
    input_label = layers.Input(shape=(1,))  # 1D label for fraud (1) or non-fraud (0)

    # Concatenate noise and label
    x = layers.Concatenate()([input_noise, input_label])

    # Generator layers
    x = layers.Dense(128, activation='relu')(x)
    x = layers.BatchNormalization()(x)
    x = layers.Dense(64, activation='relu')(x)
    x = layers.BatchNormalization()(x)
    output = layers.Dense(feature_dim, activation='tanh')(x)  # Match the feature dimensions

    return models.Model([input_noise, input_label], output)

def build_discriminator(feature_dim):
    # Feature input
    input_features = layers.Input(shape=(feature_dim,))
    # Class label input
    input_label = layers.Input(shape=(1,))

    # Concatenate features and label
    x = layers.Concatenate()([input_features, input_label])

    # Discriminator layers
    x = layers.Dense(128, activation='relu')(x)
    x = layers.Dropout(0.3)(x)
    x = layers.Dense(64, activation='relu')(x)
    x = layers.Dropout(0.3)(x)
    output = layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(x)  # Output: real (1) or fake (0)

    return models.Model([input_features, input_label], output)

def build_gan(generator, discriminator):
    discriminator.trainable = False  # Freeze discriminator during GAN training

    # GAN input
    noise_input = layers.Input(shape=(noise_dim,))
    label_input = layers.Input(shape=(1,))

    # Generator output
    generated_data = generator([noise_input, label_input])

    # Discriminator prediction
    validity = discriminator([generated_data, label_input])

    return models.Model([noise_input, label_input], validity)

# Hyperparameters
noise_dim = 100  # Size of the noise vector
data_dim = df_x_train.shape[1]  # Number of features in X

# Build models
generator = build_generator(noise_dim, data_dim)
discriminator = build_discriminator(data_dim)

# Compile discriminator
discriminator.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(0.0002, 0.5), loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

# Compile GAN
discriminator.trainable = False  # Freeze discriminator for GAN training
gan = build_gan(generator, discriminator)
gan.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(0.0002, 0.5), loss='binary_crossentropy')

def train_ccgan(generator, discriminator, gan, X_train, y_train, epochs=100000, batch_size=64):
    half_batch = batch_size // 2

    for epoch in range(epochs):
        # Train Discriminator
        idx = np.random.randint(0, X_train.shape[0], half_batch)
        real_data = X_train[idx]
        real_labels = y_train[idx]

        noise = np.random.normal(0, 1, (half_batch, noise_dim))
        fake_labels = np.random.randint(0, 2, half_batch)  # Random fraud/non-fraud labels
        fake_data = generator.predict([noise, fake_labels])

        d_loss_real = discriminator.train_on_batch([real_data, real_labels], np.ones((half_batch, 1)))
        d_loss_fake = discriminator.train_on_batch([fake_data, fake_labels], np.zeros((half_batch, 1)))
        d_loss = 0.5 * np.add(d_loss_real, d_loss_fake)

        # Train Generator
        noise = np.random.normal(0, 1, (batch_size, noise_dim))
        gen_labels = np.random.randint(0, 2, batch_size)
        g_loss = gan.train_on_batch([noise, gen_labels], np.ones((batch_size, 1)))

        # Print progress
        if epoch % 1000 == 0:
            print(f"{epoch} [D loss: {d_loss[0]} | D accuracy: {100 * d_loss[1]:.2f}%] [G loss: {g_loss}]")

# Generate synthetic fraud (1) and non-fraud (0) data with specified ratio
def generate_synthetic_data(generator, num_samples, noise_dim, fraud_ratio=0.5):
    # Calculate the number of fraud and non-fraud samples
    num_fraud = int(num_samples * fraud_ratio)
    num_non_fraud = num_samples - num_fraud

    # Generate noise and labels for fraud and non-fraud
    noise_fraud = np.random.normal(0, 1, (num_fraud, noise_dim))
    noise_non_fraud = np.random.normal(0, 1, (num_non_fraud, noise_dim))
    labels_fraud = np.ones((num_fraud, 1))
    labels_non_fraud = np.zeros((num_non_fraud, 1))

    # Generate synthetic data
    synthetic_fraud = generator.predict([noise_fraud, labels_fraud])
    synthetic_non_fraud = generator.predict([noise_non_fraud, labels_non_fraud])

    # Combine synthetic data and labels
    synthetic_data = np.vstack([synthetic_fraud, synthetic_non_fraud])
    synthetic_labels = np.vstack([labels_fraud, labels_non_fraud]).flatten()

    # Shuffle data and labels together
    shuffled_indices = np.random.permutation(len(synthetic_data))
    synthetic_data = synthetic_data[shuffled_indices]
    synthetic_labels = synthetic_labels[shuffled_indices]

    return synthetic_data, synthetic_labels

5. Optimizing the GAN

5.1 Evaluate GAN generated data

In[48]:
from scipy.stats import ks_2samp

# Store K-S statistics and p-values
ks_values = []
p_values = []

# Perform K-S test using only the training set
for col in df_x_train.columns:
    real_feature = df_x_train[col].values
    synth_feature = synthetic_df[col].values
    
    stat, p_value = ks_2samp(real_feature, synth_feature)
    ks_values.append(stat)  # Collect K-S statistic value
    p_values.append(p_value)  # Collect p-value
    
    print(f"Feature: {col}")
    print(f"K-S Test Statistic: {stat:.4f}, P-value: {p_value:.4f}")
    print("-" * 40)

# Calculate the average K-S statistic and p-value across all features

The K-S statistic value, denoted as D, represents the maximum difference between the cumulative distribution functions (CDFs) of the two datasets being compared.

Interpretation of K-S Statistic:

  • D 0 ---------> Distributions are very similar (good synthetic data)
  • D < 0.1 -------> Minor differences, synthetic data is quite close
  • 0.1 D< 0.3 ---> Moderate differences, GAN needs tuning
  • D > 0.3 -------> Significant differences, major GAN optimization needed

The p-value represents the probability that the observed difference between the real and synthetic data distributions occurred by chance.

Interpretation of P-value:

  • p > 0.05 -------> No significant difference (good synthetic data)
  • p 0.05 -------> Significant difference (synthetic data needs improvement)

# Poor TSNE
from tensorflow.keras import layers, Model, Input

# Define constants
LATENT_DIM = 32
NUM_FEATURES = 30
NUM_CLASSES = 2    # Fraud (1) and Non-fraud (0)

# Generator Model
def build_opti_generator(latent_dim=LATENT_DIM, num_classes=NUM_CLASSES, num_features=NUM_FEATURES):
    noise_input = Input(shape=(latent_dim,))
    label_input = Input(shape=(1,), dtype='int32')

    label_embed = layers.Embedding(num_classes, latent_dim)(label_input)
    label_embed = layers.Flatten()(label_embed)

    merged_input = layers.Concatenate()([noise_input, label_embed])
    x = layers.Dense(128)(merged_input)
    x = layers.LeakyReLU(0.2)(x)
    x = layers.BatchNormalization()(x)

    x = layers.Dense(256)(x)
    x = layers.LeakyReLU(0.2)(x)
    x = layers.BatchNormalization()(x)

    x = layers.Dense(512)(x)
    x = layers.LeakyReLU(0.2)(x)
    x = layers.BatchNormalization()(x)

    output = layers.Dense(num_features, activation='tanh')(x)
    model = Model([noise_input, label_input], output, name="Generator")
    return model

# Discriminator Model
def build_opti_discriminator(latent_dim=LATENT_DIM, num_classes=NUM_CLASSES, num_features=NUM_FEATURES):
    feature_input = Input(shape=(num_features,))
    label_input = Input(shape=(1,), dtype='int32')

    label_embed = layers.Embedding(num_classes, latent_dim)(label_input)
    label_embed = layers.Flatten()(label_embed)

    merged_input = layers.Concatenate()([feature_input, label_embed])
    x = layers.Dense(512)(merged_input)
    x = layers.LeakyReLU(0.2)(x)
    x = layers.LayerNormalization()(x)
    x = layers.Dropout(0.5)(x)

    x = layers.Dense(256)(x)
    x = layers.LeakyReLU(0.2)(x)
    x = layers.LayerNormalization()(x)
    x = layers.Dropout(0.4)(x)

    x = layers.Dense(128)(x)
    x = layers.LeakyReLU(0.2)(x)
    x = layers.Dropout(0.3)(x)

    output = layers.Dense(1)(x)
    model = Model([feature_input, label_input], output, name="Discriminator")
    return model

# Builder and Synthetic Data Generator
def generate_opti_synthetic_data(generator, num_samples, label_value, latent_dim=LATENT_DIM):
    noise = np.random.normal(0, 1, (num_samples, latent_dim))
    labels = np.full((num_samples, 1), label_value)
    generated_data = generator.predict([noise, labels], verbose=0)
    return generated_data

generator = build_opti_generator()
discriminator = build_opti_discriminator()

synthetic_fraud = generate_opti_synthetic_data(generator, num_samples=1000, label_value=1)
synthetic_nonfraud = generate_opti_synthetic_data(generator, num_samples=1000, label_value=0)

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras import backend as K

# --- Parameters ---
LATENT_DIM = 32
NUM_FEATURES = 30
NUM_CLASSES = 2
BATCH_SIZE = 128
EPOCHS = 2
N_CRITIC = 5  # Discriminator updates per generator update original is 5
LAMBDA_GP = 10

# --- Optimized Generator and Discriminator ---
generator = build_opti_generator()
discriminator = build_opti_discriminator()

# --- Optimizers ---
g_optimizer = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.0002, beta_1=0.5)
d_optimizer = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.0001, beta_1=0.5)

# --- Dataset preparation ---
real_data = df_x_train.values.astype(np.float32)
real_labels = df_y_train.values.astype(np.int32).reshape(-1, 1)
dataset = tf.data.Dataset.from_tensor_slices((real_data, real_labels)).shuffle(2048).batch(BATCH_SIZE).prefetch(1)

# --- Gradient Penalty ---
def gradient_penalty(real_samples, fake_samples, labels):
    alpha = tf.random.uniform([real_samples.shape[0], 1], 0.0, 1.0)
    interpolated = alpha * real_samples + (1 - alpha) * fake_samples
    with tf.GradientTape() as gp_tape:
        gp_tape.watch(interpolated)
        pred = discriminator([interpolated, labels], training=True)
    grads = gp_tape.gradient(pred, [interpolated])[0]
    norm = tf.sqrt(tf.reduce_sum(tf.square(grads), axis=1) + 1e-8)
    return tf.reduce_mean((norm - 1.0) ** 2)

# --- Training Loop ---
for epoch in range(EPOCHS):
    for i, (real_batch, label_batch) in enumerate(dataset):
        for _ in range(N_CRITIC):
            noise = tf.random.normal((real_batch.shape[0], LATENT_DIM))
            fake_data = generator([noise, label_batch], training=True)

            with tf.GradientTape() as d_tape:
                real_pred = discriminator([real_batch, label_batch], training=True)
                fake_pred = discriminator([fake_data, label_batch], training=True)
                gp = gradient_penalty(real_batch, fake_data, label_batch)
                d_loss = tf.reduce_mean(fake_pred) - tf.reduce_mean(real_pred) + LAMBDA_GP * gp

            d_grads = d_tape.gradient(d_loss, discriminator.trainable_variables)
            d_optimizer.apply_gradients(zip(d_grads, discriminator.trainable_variables))

        noise = tf.random.normal((real_batch.shape[0], LATENT_DIM))
        with tf.GradientTape() as g_tape:
            fake_data = generator([noise, label_batch], training=True)
            fake_pred = discriminator([fake_data, label_batch], training=True)
            g_loss = -tf.reduce_mean(fake_pred)

        g_grads = g_tape.gradient(g_loss, generator.trainable_variables)
        g_optimizer.apply_gradients(zip(g_grads, generator.trainable_variables))

    print(f"Epoch {epoch}, D Loss: {d_loss.numpy():.4f}, G Loss: {g_loss.numpy():.4f}")

# --- Generate Synthetic Data (Compatible with evaluation code) ---
synthetic_fraud = generate_opti_synthetic_data(generator, num_samples=1000, label_value=1)
synthetic_nonfraud = generate_opti_synthetic_data(generator, num_samples=1000, label_value=0)
synthetic_df = pd.DataFrame(np.vstack([synthetic_fraud, synthetic_nonfraud]), columns=df_x_train.columns)

from scipy.stats import ks_2samp

def evaluate_ks_test(real_df, synthetic_df):
    ks_values, p_values = [], []

    for col in real_df.columns:
        real_feature = real_df[col].values
        synth_feature = synthetic_df[col].values

        stat, p_value = ks_2samp(real_feature, synth_feature)
        ks_values.append(stat)
        p_values.append(p_value)

        print(f"Feature: {col}")
        print(f"K-S Test Statistic: {stat:.4f}, P-value: {p_value:.4f}")
        print("-" * 40)

    print(f"Average K-S Test Statistic: {np.mean(ks_values):.4f}")
    print(f"Average P-value: {np.mean(p_values):.4f}")

from scipy.spatial.distance import jensenshannon

def evaluate_jsd(real_df, synthetic_df, bins=50):
    jsd_values = []

    for col in real_df.columns:
        real_dist, _ = np.histogram(real_df[col], bins=bins, density=True)
        synth_dist, _ = np.histogram(synthetic_df[col], bins=bins, density=True)

        # Add small epsilon to avoid division by 0
        real_dist += 1e-8
        synth_dist += 1e-8

        js_div = jensenshannon(real_dist, synth_dist)
        jsd_values.append(js_div)
        print(f"Feature: {col}, JSD: {js_div:.4f}")

    print(f"\nAverage Jensen-Shannon Divergence: {np.mean(jsd_values):.4f}")

def generate_opti_synthetic_data_balanced(generator, num_samples, latent_dim=32, fraud_ratio=0.5):
    """
    Generate synthetic fraud and non-fraud data using the new optimized generator,
    and return a shuffled DataFrame with 'Class' labels.
    """
    num_fraud = int(num_samples * fraud_ratio)
    num_nonfraud = num_samples - num_fraud

    # Generate noise vectors
    noise_fraud = np.random.normal(0, 1, (num_fraud, latent_dim))
    noise_nonfraud = np.random.normal(0, 1, (num_nonfraud, latent_dim))

    # Class labels
    labels_fraud = np.ones((num_fraud, 1), dtype=int)
    labels_nonfraud = np.zeros((num_nonfraud, 1), dtype=int)

    # Generate samples using the new GAN generator
    synthetic_fraud = generator.predict([noise_fraud, labels_fraud], verbose=0)
    synthetic_nonfraud = generator.predict([noise_nonfraud, labels_nonfraud], verbose=0)

    # Combine and shuffle
    X_synth = np.vstack([synthetic_fraud, synthetic_nonfraud])
    y_synth = np.vstack([labels_fraud, labels_nonfraud]).flatten()

    indices = np.random.permutation(len(X_synth))
    X_synth = X_synth[indices]
    y_synth = y_synth[indices]

    # Convert to DataFrame
    synthetic_df = pd.DataFrame(X_synth, columns=df_x_train.columns)
    synthetic_df["Class"] = y_synth.astype(int)

    return synthetic_df

# Generate synthetic dataset with the new GAN, 220,000 samples, 85% fraud
synthetic_df = generate_opti_synthetic_data_balanced(generator, num_samples=220000, latent_dim=LATENT_DIM, fraud_ratio=0.85)

# Inspect class balance

#testing on synthetic + real data
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.utils.class_weight import compute_class_weight
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, confusion_matrix, roc_auc_score
from lightgbm import LGBMClassifier
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense, Dropout
from tensorflow.keras.callbacks import EarlyStopping

# Step 1: Combine real and synthetic data
X_combined = np.vstack([df_x_train.values, X_synth])
y_combined = np.hstack([df_y_train.values, y_synth])

# Step 2: Split combined data
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
    X_combined, y_combined, test_size=0.2, stratify=y_combined, random_state=42
)

# Step 3: Train LGBM and get predicted probabilities
lgbm = LGBMClassifier(n_estimators=100, learning_rate=0.1, random_state=42)
lgbm.fit(X_train, y_train)

proba_train = lgbm.predict_proba(X_train)[:, 1].reshape(-1, 1)
proba_test = lgbm.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1].reshape(-1, 1)

# Step 4: Augment original features with LGBM predicted scores
X_train_hybrid = np.hstack([X_train, proba_train])
X_test_hybrid = np.hstack([X_test, proba_test])

# Step 5: Compute class weights
class_weights = compute_class_weight(class_weight='balanced', classes=np.unique(y_train), y=y_train)
class_weight_dict = {i: weight for i, weight in enumerate(class_weights)}

# Step 6: Define and compile the DNN
def build_dnn_model(input_dim):
    model = Sequential([
        Dense(128, activation='relu', input_shape=(input_dim,)),
        Dropout(0.3),
        Dense(64, activation='relu'),
        Dropout(0.3),
        Dense(32, activation='relu'),
        Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')
    ])
    return model

dnn_model = build_dnn_model(X_train_hybrid.shape[1])
dnn_model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy', tf.keras.metrics.AUC(name='auc')])

# Step 7: Train the DNN
early_stop = EarlyStopping(patience=5, restore_best_weights=True, monitor='val_auc', mode='max')

history = dnn_model.fit(
    X_train_hybrid, y_train,
    validation_data=(X_test_hybrid, y_test),
    epochs=50,
    batch_size=128,
    class_weight=class_weight_dict,
    callbacks=[early_stop],
    verbose=1
)

# Step 8: Evaluate the hybrid model
y_pred_proba = dnn_model.predict(X_test_hybrid).flatten()
y_pred_class = (y_pred_proba >= 0.5).astype(int)

print("Confusion Matrix:")
print(confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_class))

print("\nClassification Report:")
print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred_class))

print("Hybrid LGBM-DNN ROC-AUC Score:", roc_auc_score(y_test, y_pred_proba))

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.utils.class_weight import compute_class_weight
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, confusion_matrix, roc_auc_score
from lightgbm import LGBMClassifier
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense, Dropout, BatchNormalization
from tensorflow.keras.callbacks import EarlyStopping

# Step 1: Combine real and synthetic data
X_combined = np.vstack([df_x_train.values, X_synth])
y_combined = np.hstack([df_y_train.values, y_synth])

# Step 2: Split combined data
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
    X_combined, y_combined, test_size=0.2, stratify=y_combined, random_state=42
)

# Step 3: Train LGBM with tuned hyperparameters
lgbm = LGBMClassifier(
    n_estimators=200,
    learning_rate=0.05,
    max_depth=6,
    scale_pos_weight=0.75,  # Adjusts class weighting inside LGBM
    subsample=0.8,
    colsample_bytree=0.8,
    random_state=42
)
lgbm.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Evaluate LGBM alone
proba_train = lgbm.predict_proba(X_train)[:, 1].reshape(-1, 1)
proba_test = lgbm.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1].reshape(-1, 1)
print("LGBM ROC-AUC:", roc_auc_score(y_test, proba_test))

# Step 4: Augment features with LGBM probabilities
X_train_hybrid = np.hstack([X_train, proba_train])
X_test_hybrid = np.hstack([X_test, proba_test])

# Step 5: Adjust class weights (manual tuning)
class_weight_dict = {0: 0.6, 1: 0.4}  # Custom balanced

# Step 6: Define optimized DNN
def build_dnn_model(input_dim):
    model = Sequential([
        Dense(128, activation='relu', input_shape=(input_dim,)),
        BatchNormalization(),
        Dropout(0.2),
        Dense(64, activation='relu'),
        BatchNormalization(),
        Dropout(0.2),
        Dense(32, activation='relu'),
        Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')
    ])
    return model

dnn_model = build_dnn_model(X_train_hybrid.shape[1])
dnn_model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy', tf.keras.metrics.AUC(name='auc')])

# Step 7: Train DNN
early_stop = EarlyStopping(patience=5, restore_best_weights=True, monitor='val_auc', mode='max')

history = dnn_model.fit(
    X_train_hybrid, y_train,
    validation_data=(X_test_hybrid, y_test),
    epochs=50,
    batch_size=128,
    class_weight=class_weight_dict,
    callbacks=[early_stop],
    verbose=1
)

# Step 8: Evaluate the hybrid model
from sklearn.metrics import precision_recall_curve

# Step 8: Evaluate the hybrid model
y_pred_proba = dnn_model.predict(X_test_hybrid).flatten()

# Automatically find the best threshold by F1-score
from sklearn.metrics import f1_score

best_f1 = 0
best_threshold = 0.5
for t in np.arange(0.1, 0.9, 0.01):
    preds = (y_pred_proba >= t).astype(int)
    f1 = f1_score(y_test, preds)
    if f1 > best_f1:
        best_f1 = f1
        best_threshold = t

print(f"\nBest threshold by F1: {best_threshold:.2f} with F1: {best_f1:.4f}")

# Evaluate using the best threshold
y_pred_custom = (y_pred_proba >= best_threshold).astype(int)

print("\nConfusion Matrix (Best Threshold):")
print(confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_custom))

print("\nClassification Report (Best Threshold):")
print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred_custom))

print("Hybrid LGBM-DNN ROC-AUC Score:", roc_auc_score(y_test, y_pred_proba))  # AUC doesn't depend on threshold

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import joblib
import tensorflow as tf
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, confusion_matrix, roc_auc_score, f1_score

# --- Load models ---
# 1. Augmented Baseline DNN (trained on synthetic + real data)
aug_dnn_model = tf.keras.models.load_model("aug_baseline_dnn_model.keras")

# 2. Optimized Hybrid Model
lgbm = joblib.load("opti_lgbm_model.pkl")
hybrid_dnn_model = tf.keras.models.load_model("opti_hybrid_dnn_model.keras")

# --- Prepare evaluation inputs ---

# For aug_dnn_model (expects 30 features)
X_val_real = df_x_val.values  # shape: (n_samples, 30)

# For hybrid_dnn_model (expects 31 features, last = LGBM predicted prob)
lgbm_val_probs = lgbm.predict_proba(df_x_val)[:, 1].reshape(-1, 1)
X_val_hybrid = np.hstack([X_val_real, lgbm_val_probs])  # shape: (n_samples, 31)

# --- Predict and evaluate Augmented Baseline DNN Model ---
aug_preds_prob = aug_dnn_model.predict(X_val_real).flatten()
aug_preds_class = (aug_preds_prob >= 0.5).astype(int)

print("=== Augmented Baseline DNN Model ===")
print("ROC-AUC:", roc_auc_score(df_y_val, aug_preds_prob))
print("F1-score:", f1_score(df_y_val, aug_preds_class))
print("Confusion Matrix:\n", confusion_matrix(df_y_val, aug_preds_class))
print("Classification Report:\n", classification_report(df_y_val, aug_preds_class))

# --- Predict and evaluate Optimized Hybrid LGBM-DNN Model ---
hyb_preds_prob = hybrid_dnn_model.predict(X_val_hybrid).flatten()
hyb_preds_class = (hyb_preds_prob >= 0.5).astype(int)

print("\n=== Optimized Hybrid LGBM-DNN Model ===")
print("ROC-AUC:", roc_auc_score(df_y_val, hyb_preds_prob))
print("F1-score:", f1_score(df_y_val, hyb_preds_class))
print("Confusion Matrix:\n", confusion_matrix(df_y_val, hyb_preds_class))
print("Classification Report:\n", classification_report(df_y_val, hyb_preds_class))

8. Conclusion and Future Work

This project successfully explored the use of GAN-augmented data in credit card fraud detection and implemented an effective hybrid LGBM-DNN model. The evaluation results demonstrated that both models, when trained on combined real and synthetic data, achieved strong performance in terms of AUC-ROC and F1-score.

However, there remains potential for further optimization and enhancement:

  • GAN Optimization:

    • Training with more epochs (given sufficient computational time).
    • Applying Wasserstein GAN with gradient penalty for better training stability.
    • Incorporating domain-specific feature guidance, such as transaction time, amount, or noise variance control to diversify the generated samples.
    • Experimenting with advanced loss functions and progressive training.

  • LGBM-DNN Hybrid Enhancements:

    • Using Bayesian optimization or Optuna for automated hyperparameter tuning.
    • Trying ensemble methods (e.g., stacking other classifiers with DNN).
    • Exploring feature selection to reduce noise and improve model generalization.

Additionally, the Streamlit application developed provides an interactive way to deploy the trained models. While it currently requires a dataset with exactly 30 features (excluding the Class label), future improvements could include:

  • Automatically detecting and adapting to different input feature shapes.
  • Providing column mapping UI to support varied datasets.
  • Supporting real-time or batch scoring with live visualization of fraud probability distributions.

These improvements would make the system more robust, scalable, and user-friendly for deployment in real-world fraud detection scenarios.
